The paper discusses data structures for text indexing, which is a topic in computer science that falls under several sub-categories. The use of suffix trees and suffix arrays suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AL (Computational Complexity). The mention of "answering queries" and "online version of indexing" suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.DM (Data Mining). Finally, the mention of worst-case deterministic time bounds suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.CC, cs.DM, and cs.AL, in that order.
